00:12:46.807 --> 00:12:48.517
All right. When you're ready.

250
00:12:51.145 --> 00:12:53.272
I murdered my husband. Santiago del Río.

251
00:12:53.355 --> 00:12:54.440
[tense music playing]

252
00:12:54.523 --> 00:12:57.485
Ángela Ferrer only helped me
to get rid of his body.

253
00:12:58.194 --> 00:12:59.570
By making this statement…

254
00:13:02.990 --> 00:13:04.909
she's being cleared of any responsibility.

255
00:13:06.285 --> 00:13:08.037
I acted in self-defense.

256
00:13:08.120 --> 00:13:10.372
He was going to kill Ángela.
so I shot him.

257
00:13:13.501 --> 00:13:14.752
[sobbing]

258
00:13:19.715 --> 00:13:20.549
[music ends]

259
00:13:21.133 --> 00:13:23.219
I know you're seeing someone.

260
00:13:24.261 --> 00:13:27.431
and she doesn't appreciate you
the same way I do.

261
00:13:28.098 --> 00:13:31.685
Just remember. I have eyes everywhere.

262
00:13:32.853 --> 00:13:33.687
Now tell me…

263
00:13:35.981 --> 00:13:38.150
who's the bitch you're sleeping with?

264
00:13:39.318 --> 00:13:41.070
Besides me. [laughs]

265
00:13:41.153 --> 00:13:42.863
[upbeat music playing]

266
00:13:43.405 --> 00:13:44.323
Who is it?

267
00:13:44.406 --> 00:13:47.076
- [singing in Spanish]
- [audience applauding. cheering]

268
00:14:15.688 --> 00:14:16.981
[cheering]

269
00:14:33.914 --> 00:14:34.957
[knocking]

270
00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:36.125
[Camila] Come in!

271
00:14:42.798 --> 00:14:44.133
I needed to see you.

272
00:14:44.216 --> 00:14:46.176
You can't escape from me. Camila.

273
00:14:47.011 --> 00:14:47.845
[Camila sighs]

274
00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:49.805
Are you leaving?

275
00:14:50.806 --> 00:14:52.558
Yes. actually.

276
00:14:52.641 --> 00:14:55.603
I have to go and pick Eva up from a party.

277
00:14:55.686 --> 00:14:57.229
If you want. we can speak later.

278
00:14:57.313 --> 00:14:58.314
I'll go with you.

279
00:14:59.982 --> 00:15:01.108
[chuckles]

280
00:15:01.191 --> 00:15:04.862
[Noa continues singing in Spanish]

281
00:15:06.196 --> 00:15:07.907
[audience cheering]

282
00:15:18.709 --> 00:15:20.377
- [music ends]
- [audience cheering]

283
00:15:20.461 --> 00:15:22.504
[Oliver] Isn't it more than a coincidence?

284
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:25.758
You're in a crisis with Miguel.
and I'm going through hell with Joanna.

285
00:15:25.841 --> 00:15:27.676
[Camila] I didn't know
things were bad with her.

286
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:30.888
[Oliver] We haven't been happy for years.
but my problems with Joanna are

287
00:15:30.971 --> 00:15:31.972
because of you.

288
00:15:32.056 --> 00:15:34.934
I've been having doubts
ever since you and I met.

289
00:15:35.643 --> 00:15:37.144
The moment I saw you.

290
00:15:39.730 --> 00:15:40.648
[Camila sighs]

291
00:15:41.523 --> 00:15:42.358
What?

292
00:15:44.443 --> 00:15:47.905
It's unfair that you're blaming me
for your problems. That's all.

293
00:15:48.405 --> 00:15:50.658
So why am I here and not in bed with her?

294
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:56.038
I'll admit. well…
there's an attraction we share.

295
00:15:56.747 --> 00:15:58.332
but that's all. Oliver.

296
00:16:00.334 --> 00:16:01.293
Fine. then.

297
00:16:02.836 --> 00:16:06.298
I'm happy you can acknowledge that.
and I think… [inhales sharply]

298
00:16:07.424 --> 00:16:08.425
…that's progress.

299
00:16:09.051 --> 00:16:11.637
The progress. Oliver. would be
for you to understand

300
00:16:11.720 --> 00:16:13.597
that nothing's going to happen between us.

301
00:16:13.681 --> 00:16:15.432
Oh. Camila. it's happening.

302
00:16:15.516 --> 00:16:16.934
[mellow music playing]

303
00:16:17.017 --> 00:16:18.978
And it's not physical or sexual.

304
00:16:19.061 --> 00:16:20.479
No. yeah. not at all.

305
00:16:22.648 --> 00:16:23.649
It's happening here.

306
00:16:26.151 --> 00:16:27.069
And in here.

307
00:16:32.908 --> 00:16:34.326
- [Micaela] Bye.
- [woman] Take care.

308
00:16:36.704 --> 00:16:38.247
- [Camila] Hi! How are you?
- Hi.

309
00:16:38.872 --> 00:16:41.291
I'm Camila. I'm here to pick up Eva.

310
00:16:41.375 --> 00:16:43.168
- Hi.
- Hello.

311
00:16:43.252 --> 00:16:46.171
So could you tell her
that I'm outside waiting for her. please?

312
00:16:46.255 --> 00:16:48.549
I've been looking for her.
wondering where she was.

313
00:16:48.632 --> 00:16:49.967
but she never showed up.

314
00:16:50.050 --> 00:16:50.884
[tense music playing]

315
00:16:50.968 --> 00:16:52.428
What do you mean? I brought her here.

316
00:16:52.511 --> 00:16:54.555
She went down the stairs.
I watched her go in.

317
00:16:54.638 --> 00:16:56.432
No. Mica spent the whole night
waiting for her.

318
00:16:56.515 --> 00:16:58.058
She really wasn't here.

319
00:16:58.142 --> 00:16:59.101
No. wait. Let me see.

320
00:16:59.184 --> 00:17:03.313
Uh. here.
I… I took a picture of her. She was here.

321
00:17:03.397 --> 00:17:05.691
See. she's just outside here.

322
00:17:06.817 --> 00:17:09.278
I don't know
because no one saw her tonight.

323
00:17:09.361 --> 00:17:10.696
[tense music playing]

324
00:17:10.779 --> 00:17:12.781
No. let me call. [exhales]

325
00:17:13.532 --> 00:17:14.408
Uh. please.

326
00:17:14.491 --> 00:17:16.410
Hi. Eva. It's Camila.
I'm worried about you.

327
00:17:16.493 --> 00:17:18.787
I came to pick you up.
but I'm with Micaela now.

328
00:17:18.871 --> 00:17:21.540
Please. tell me where you are?
Answer the phone now.

329
00:17:23.000 --> 00:17:23.834
Are you sure?

330
00:17:23.917 --> 00:17:26.045
'Cause maybe you didn't see her inside.
I don't know.

331
00:17:26.128 --> 00:17:27.546
- No.
- She wasn't here.

332
00:17:30.841 --> 00:17:34.094
[pop music playing]

333
00:17:35.429 --> 00:17:37.598
[Tom] There's a crazy woman
who wants to meet you.

334
00:17:37.681 --> 00:17:40.350
She said she's willing to pay any amount.

335
00:17:40.434 --> 00:17:41.435
And she is?

336
00:17:43.896 --> 00:17:45.898
<i>♪ I need you… ♪</i>

337
00:17:46.982 --> 00:17:48.525
[woman] You were amazing!

338
00:17:49.276 --> 00:17:50.903
Absolutely divine.

339
00:17:51.737 --> 00:17:55.157
<i>♪ Never let me out of sight</i>
<i>Out of mind. out of touch ♪</i>

340
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:57.367
<i>♪ Don't throw me away ♪</i>

341
00:17:58.202 --> 00:18:00.913
<i>♪ I know that you'll treat me so well… ♪</i>

342
00:18:01.455 --> 00:18:02.664
[Noa] Good evening.

343
00:18:02.748 --> 00:18:04.041
You wanted to see me?

344
00:18:05.417 --> 00:18:06.627
Wow.

345
00:18:07.753 --> 00:18:10.547
The great Jade Monroe.

346
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:13.092
I've wanted to see you for a long time.

347
00:18:13.175 --> 00:18:14.426
You're very popular.

348
00:18:14.510 --> 00:18:16.970
[Noa] Well. thank you very much.

349
00:18:17.054 --> 00:18:18.722
How can I help you tonight?

350
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.478
You have no idea. do you?

351
00:18:24.561 --> 00:18:26.355
[pop song continues]

352
00:18:26.438 --> 00:18:28.649
You don't know who I am? Really?

353
00:18:29.817 --> 00:18:34.196
So I play characters for fun. you know.
but. hi. I am Ángela Ferrer.

354
00:18:34.279 --> 00:18:38.784
and if you keep playing house with Inti.
I'm going to be your worst nightmare.

355
00:18:38.867 --> 00:18:40.327
[dramatic sting]

356
00:18:41.703 --> 00:18:45.999
- Madam. is this a threat? Truly?
- Oh. I don't threaten.

357
00:18:46.083 --> 00:18:47.626
Instead. I act.

358
00:18:48.669 --> 00:18:52.548
I imagine your boy toy has told you
a few good things about me. yes?

359
00:18:52.631 --> 00:18:54.967
Everyone talks about you. You're famous.

360
00:18:55.050 --> 00:18:58.262
- Wow? I'm infamous.
- Yes. [laughs]

361
00:19:00.347 --> 00:19:01.932
Inti belongs to me.

362
00:19:02.015 --> 00:19:05.686
He can fuck you if that's his thing.
but he's all mine.

363
00:19:05.769 --> 00:19:08.230
- Hmm?
- [laughing]

364
00:19:08.313 --> 00:19:10.107
Oh. my love.

365
00:19:10.190 --> 00:19:12.860
Don't laugh like that. Noa. please.

366
00:19:13.652 --> 00:19:16.155
Go on and smell.
Do you catch Inti's scent?

367
00:19:17.698 --> 00:19:22.744
We had a spectacular experience together
in a hotel.

368
00:19:22.828 --> 00:19:25.247
We haven't had
such a great time in a while.

369
00:19:29.585 --> 00:19:33.130
You're quite lucky
because you should be dead by now.

370
00:19:34.173 --> 00:19:35.174
[dramatic sting]

371
00:19:39.386 --> 00:19:41.346
[cell phone ringing]

372
00:19:48.145 --> 00:19:49.605
[woman] <i>Eva's been kidnapped.</i>

373
00:19:51.356 --> 00:19:52.232
[music ends]

374
00:19:53.108 --> 00:19:54.902
[cell phone ringing]

375
00:20:01.867 --> 00:20:02.784
{\an8}[cell phone chiming]

376
00:20:02.868 --> 00:20:08.248
{\an8}PLEASE COME RIGHT AWAY. EVA IS MISSING.

377
00:20:08.749 --> 00:20:09.583
{\an8}[groans]

378
00:20:16.298 --> 00:20:17.424
[exhales]

379
00:20:21.720 --> 00:20:22.971
[upbeat music playing]

380
00:20:23.055 --> 00:20:25.682
You know. I've been thinking about
everything that's happened

381
00:20:25.766 --> 00:20:27.142
these past few weeks.

382
00:20:29.061 --> 00:20:30.479
The feel of your body.

383
00:20:33.732 --> 00:20:35.567
I can't stop thinking about it.

384
00:20:36.360 --> 00:20:38.362
- That's what you want?
- [exhales]

385
00:20:39.404 --> 00:20:43.367
Oh. Alonso.
even if I wanted to reject you.

386
00:20:43.450 --> 00:20:44.493
I wouldn't.

387
00:20:45.535 --> 00:20:46.662
I couldn't.

388
00:20:47.579 --> 00:20:48.747
You're my drug.

389
00:20:51.750 --> 00:20:53.043
What is it you're saying?

390
00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:57.756
I don't know.

391
00:20:59.091 --> 00:21:02.886
I… I actually want to. I don't know.

392
00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:06.056
give us another chance?

393
00:21:07.933 --> 00:21:09.434
Are you being serious?

394
00:21:09.977 --> 00:21:10.894
No. [laughing]

395
00:21:13.230 --> 00:21:16.316
It's the wine
or the food. the lobster we ate.

396
00:21:16.400 --> 00:21:17.859
Yeah. that's it. Of course it is.

397
00:21:17.943 --> 00:21:19.236
[laughing]

398
00:21:20.988 --> 00:21:22.531
I want to be happy. Alonso.

399
00:21:22.614 --> 00:21:23.824
[romantic music playing]

400
00:21:25.826 --> 00:21:28.120
Even if it's hard for me to trust you.

401
00:21:29.705 --> 00:21:31.081
I do love being with you.

402
00:21:31.164 --> 00:21:33.333
And I love being with you. Laura.

403
00:21:35.585 --> 00:21:37.504
And I know that right now.

404
00:21:37.587 --> 00:21:40.632
it may be difficult
for you to believe this.

405
00:21:42.968 --> 00:21:44.303
but I swear to you.

406
00:21:45.387 --> 00:21:46.680
I'm gonna make you happy.

407
00:21:47.180 --> 00:21:49.141
I wanna make you the happiest woman

408
00:21:50.267 --> 00:21:51.351
in the world.

409
00:22:06.783 --> 00:22:07.659
[music ends]

410
00:22:07.743 --> 00:22:09.786
- [sirens wailing]
- [indistinct radio chatter]

411
00:22:12.080 --> 00:22:12.956
Where's Eva?

412
00:22:14.166 --> 00:22:16.668
- Hold on. I'll tell you what happened.
- Where is she? Where's Eva?

413
00:22:16.752 --> 00:22:19.796
- [Ángela sobbing]
- I… I took her to the party.

414
00:22:20.297 --> 00:22:22.632
I watched Eva go inside.
and I took a picture of her.

415
00:22:22.716 --> 00:22:24.301
- I swear she went in.
- And then?

416
00:22:24.384 --> 00:22:25.635
[Camila] She just disappeared.

417
00:22:25.719 --> 00:22:29.056
Camila decided to take her to a party
without our permission.

418
00:22:29.848 --> 00:22:32.642
Micaela. please ask around.
There's no way that no one saw her.

419
00:22:32.726 --> 00:22:34.436
For God's sake. just ask around!

420
00:22:34.519 --> 00:22:35.604
[Ángela breathing heavily]

421
00:22:36.229 --> 00:22:37.147
For God's sake.

422
00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:38.565
- [man] Are you Eva's parents?
- Yes.

423
00:22:38.648 --> 00:22:40.275
- What is it?
- I am. yes. You have news?

424
00:22:40.359 --> 00:22:42.402
We have recordings
from the security camera.

425
00:22:42.486 --> 00:22:44.571
[tense music playing]

426
00:22:46.782 --> 00:22:48.033
- She went inside?
- She entered.

427
00:22:48.116 --> 00:22:49.868
She went in. That's what I told you.

428
00:22:49.951 --> 00:22:52.120
I took a photo.
and I made sure she went inside.

429
00:22:52.204 --> 00:22:54.373
- [Miguel] Then what?
- [man] Hold on. just a second.

430
00:23:06.593 --> 00:23:07.761
No!

431
00:23:07.844 --> 00:23:09.221
Oh. motherfucker!

432
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:12.307
- Oh.
- Oh. my God. Eva.

433
00:23:16.728 --> 00:23:17.562
[music ends]

434
00:23:17.646 --> 00:23:19.481
Are we such bad parents?

435
00:23:25.153 --> 00:23:26.154
[Ángela] Of course not.

436
00:23:31.326 --> 00:23:32.411
[breathing shakily]

437
00:23:34.538 --> 00:23:35.539
Then why…

438
00:23:38.625 --> 00:23:40.335
Why's this happening to us?

439
00:23:49.136 --> 00:23:51.388
[Ángela] I'm sure everything will be fine.

440
00:23:59.604 --> 00:24:01.273
Then where's Eva. Ángela?

441
00:24:04.484 --> 00:24:05.527
Do you know?

442
00:24:07.446 --> 00:24:09.322
I wish I knew where she was.

443
00:24:11.324 --> 00:24:12.784
Are you sure you don't know?

444
00:24:12.868 --> 00:24:14.327
[tense music playing]

445
00:24:15.203 --> 00:24:16.204
Excuse me?

446
00:24:17.789 --> 00:24:19.708
Are you blaming me for this now?

447
00:24:20.333 --> 00:24:21.960
I don't know who I can trust.

448
00:24:24.129 --> 00:24:25.630
I do know one thing.

449
00:24:27.674 --> 00:24:30.260
Your last name provokes a lot of hatred.

450
00:24:31.761 --> 00:24:32.804
[Ángela] Mmm.

451
00:24:32.888 --> 00:24:34.556
Are you sure you don't know?

452
00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:39.269
Is there anyone you suspect at all?

453
00:24:44.232 --> 00:24:49.029
The fact that you could actually believe
I would is outrageous.

454
00:24:51.490 --> 00:24:53.742
What kind of person do you think I am?

455
00:24:57.204 --> 00:24:58.371
[inhales deeply]

456
00:25:00.916 --> 00:25:02.042
I swear to you…

457
00:25:03.293 --> 00:25:05.295
[music fades]

458
00:25:05.378 --> 00:25:06.588
…wherever she is.

459
00:25:07.839 --> 00:25:09.633
I will find her. Ángela.

460
00:25:10.217 --> 00:25:11.301
I hope you do.

461
00:25:14.554 --> 00:25:16.181
[doorbell ringing]

462
00:25:25.607 --> 00:25:26.441
[door opens]

463
00:25:28.693 --> 00:25:30.862
- [Vannessa] Ángela.
- Vannessa.

464
00:25:30.946 --> 00:25:31.905
Are you alone?

465
00:25:31.988 --> 00:25:34.407
- Mmm. Miguel's in the other room. why?
- Well…

466
00:25:35.242 --> 00:25:36.618
[inhales deeply]

467
00:25:36.701 --> 00:25:38.119
I just came to give you my support.

468
00:25:38.203 --> 00:25:42.290
I imagine…
how hard all of this must be for you.

469
00:25:43.250 --> 00:25:44.167
Thank you.

470
00:25:45.669 --> 00:25:47.754
[inhales. exhales]

471
00:25:47.837 --> 00:25:49.005
[dramatic sting]

472
00:25:49.089 --> 00:25:53.051
Ángela will easily let you
take all of the blame.

473
00:25:54.386 --> 00:25:55.470
Hand her over to me.

474
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:59.558
and I can assure you
that you will raise your children.

475
00:26:01.142 --> 00:26:03.144
[dramatic sting]

476
00:26:03.687 --> 00:26:04.563
I'm sorry.

477
00:26:05.230 --> 00:26:06.648
The guilt was too much for me.

478
00:26:07.482 --> 00:26:09.859
If I kept lying.
I would've fallen apart completely

479
00:26:09.943 --> 00:26:10.819
sooner or later.

480
00:26:11.528 --> 00:26:12.696
I went to the police.

481
00:26:12.779 --> 00:26:13.863
[tense music playing]

482
00:26:19.160 --> 00:26:19.995
Could you…

483
00:26:22.289 --> 00:26:23.748
just say something.

484
00:26:23.832 --> 00:26:24.666
Anything.

485
00:26:26.042 --> 00:26:28.712
Right now.
my mind is on how to find my daughter.

486
00:26:28.795 --> 00:26:30.130
I need to find Eva.

487
00:26:31.590 --> 00:26:32.424
Okay.

488
00:26:33.133 --> 00:26:34.092
Excuse me.

489
00:26:42.851 --> 00:26:44.603
[tense music building]

490
00:26:50.942 --> 00:26:51.818
[music ends]

491
00:26:54.487 --> 00:26:55.530
[car door closes]

492
00:27:06.708 --> 00:27:07.584
[Norris] Hey.

493
00:27:10.003 --> 00:27:11.713
[man] Here's what we agreed on.

494
00:27:15.884 --> 00:27:16.718
Okay.

495
00:27:19.929 --> 00:27:21.431
[intriguing music playing]

496
00:27:32.776 --> 00:27:33.610
[man] Go ahead.

497
00:27:35.236 --> 00:27:36.404
[gun firing]

498
00:27:39.574 --> 00:27:41.076
[tense music playing]

499
00:27:47.707 --> 00:27:48.541
[music ends]

500
00:27:50.085 --> 00:27:53.797
Who the hell told me
I could play house and take care of a kid?

501
00:27:54.631 --> 00:27:55.632
Why. David?

502
00:27:55.715 --> 00:27:58.593
Why did I think I could be her mother
when I'm obviously not?

503
00:27:59.094 --> 00:28:02.055
You know what?
I think you will make a wonderful mother.

504
00:28:02.138 --> 00:28:04.391
David. come on. [sighs]

505
00:28:04.474 --> 00:28:07.560
Look. really.
Eva is a sweet and lovely girl.

506
00:28:07.644 --> 00:28:09.938
She's a lonely kid.
and I feel so much for her.

507
00:28:10.021 --> 00:28:11.398
but she has a flaw.

508
00:28:11.481 --> 00:28:12.649
It's a big one.

509
00:28:12.732 --> 00:28:16.695
She's a Ferrer.
and her mom is a fucking psycho.

510
00:28:17.946 --> 00:28:19.197
What am I gonna do?

511
00:28:20.281 --> 00:28:21.199
Excuse me.

512
00:28:22.033 --> 00:28:25.787
- Camila. how are you?
- I'm very worried about Eva.

513
00:28:25.870 --> 00:28:28.289
She's missing. nowhere to be found.

514
00:28:29.332 --> 00:28:31.334
[David] I don't believe we've met before.

515
00:28:31.418 --> 00:28:33.545
Although. I've seen you around.

516
00:28:33.628 --> 00:28:35.880
but of course
your clothes were missing. [laughs]

517
00:28:35.964 --> 00:28:37.340
[Oliver laughs] Nice to meet you.

518
00:28:38.466 --> 00:28:39.467
It's David. right?

519
00:28:39.968 --> 00:28:40.969
David.

520
00:28:41.469 --> 00:28:43.930
<i>♪ Madness ♪</i>

521
00:28:44.013 --> 00:28:47.183
[Ángela] It's been almost 12 hours.

522
00:28:47.684 --> 00:28:50.854
And we still haven't had
any contact with the kidnappers.

523
00:28:50.937 --> 00:28:52.772
Hmm. That's strange.

524
00:28:53.648 --> 00:28:58.445
If Eva had just stayed at the house.
none of this would have happened.

525
00:28:58.528 --> 00:29:00.822
[Miguel] They could've taken her
from anywhere. Ángela.

526
00:29:00.905 --> 00:29:01.740
It's our fault.

527
00:29:01.823 --> 00:29:03.658
We're both responsible.

528
00:29:04.159 --> 00:29:05.326
Well. I was working.

529
00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:07.370
- [Miguel] Ah. you were working.
- Mm-hmm.

530
00:29:08.830 --> 00:29:10.999
You were working at the Marriott Hotel?

531
00:29:13.793 --> 00:29:15.795
Yes. I had a few things to finish.

532
00:29:16.296 --> 00:29:18.465
You were at the deluxe suite
at the Marriott

533
00:29:19.048 --> 00:29:21.885
with a man. Inti Valderrama.

534
00:29:21.968 --> 00:29:24.304
[dramatic sting]

535
00:29:25.221 --> 00:29:26.639
What does this have to do with Eva?

536
00:29:26.723 --> 00:29:29.100
- Well…
- And who put you in charge of finding her?

537
00:29:29.684 --> 00:29:30.769
Because I requested it

538
00:29:30.852 --> 00:29:34.397
since I know the family
and work with the anti-kidnapping unit.

539
00:29:34.481 --> 00:29:37.275
Honestly. I'd prefer
if someone else could be in charge

540
00:29:37.358 --> 00:29:40.153
because you have issues with me.
and you can't be fair to us.

541
00:29:40.236 --> 00:29:41.070
[Miguel] Ángela.

542
00:29:41.905 --> 00:29:43.990
this isn't about you. damn it.

543
00:29:44.616 --> 00:29:46.743
The important thing here is to find Eva.

544
00:29:46.826 --> 00:29:47.660
That's all.

545
00:29:47.744 --> 00:29:48.870
[dramatic sting]

546
00:29:53.374 --> 00:29:56.252
[Noa sighs] You need
to move out of my house.

547
00:29:56.336 --> 00:29:57.962
I talked to Ángela Ferrer.

548
00:29:58.046 --> 00:29:59.964
- Oh. that's good.
- Yes. great.

549
00:30:01.174 --> 00:30:03.802
She said you had sex at a hotel.

550
00:30:04.511 --> 00:30:06.179
Huh? No. Oh. no. no.

551
00:30:06.262 --> 00:30:07.514
- She told me everything.
- Ah. no.

552
00:30:07.597 --> 00:30:10.767
We were at a hotel. but. no. please.
Nothing happened.

553
00:30:10.850 --> 00:30:12.268
Inti. what should I make of this?

554
00:30:12.894 --> 00:30:14.437
She told me I should be dead.

555
00:30:15.396 --> 00:30:16.439
[chuckles] No.

556
00:30:16.523 --> 00:30:18.191
Oh. Ángela. [laughs]

557
00:30:19.192 --> 00:30:21.986
Ángela's. like. a little crazy. you know?

558
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:24.239
- I apologize.
- Apologize?

559
00:30:26.032 --> 00:30:27.617
Stop pretending. okay?

560
00:30:28.284 --> 00:30:29.911
You said you apologized.

561
00:30:29.994 --> 00:30:32.121
I don't believe you at all. Inti.

562
00:30:32.622 --> 00:30:35.792
I've made my decision.
and you have got to go.

563
00:30:35.875 --> 00:30:36.835
I don't want you around.

564
00:30:37.710 --> 00:30:39.212
<i>♪ My knees were on the floor ♪</i>

565
00:30:40.588 --> 00:30:42.966
<i>♪ Praying you would want me more ♪</i>

566
00:30:43.716 --> 00:30:46.177
<i>♪ Not like girls you've met before ♪</i>

567
00:30:46.261 --> 00:30:48.555
<i>♪ There's something twisted in my mind ♪</i>

568
00:30:48.638 --> 00:30:50.765
<i>♪ In my mind ♪</i>

569
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:51.933
<i>♪ Broke both my wrists ♪</i>

570
00:30:52.016 --> 00:30:53.518
<i>♪ You dodged my kiss… ♪</i>

571
00:30:54.811 --> 00:30:56.813
[suspenseful music playing]

572
00:31:02.610 --> 00:31:04.237
[Camila groans]

573
00:31:04.904 --> 00:31:06.865
[both grunting]

574
00:31:08.867 --> 00:31:09.909
